<p>According to the approached proposed by Rapaport,
 <xref rid="cphc202000498-bib-0076" ref-type="ref">
  <sup>[76]</sup>
 </xref> the dynamics of breaking and making of hydrogen bonds can be quantified in terms of the continuous HB time correlation function (TCF), 
 <bold>S</bold>
 <sub>HB</sub>(
 <bold>t</bold>), which gives the probability that a pair, 
 <bold>i</bold> and 
 <bold>j</bold>, remains continuously hydrogen‐bonded from 0 to 
 <bold>t</bold>:[
 <xref rid="cphc202000498-bib-0029" ref-type="ref">
  <sup>29</sup>
 </xref>, 
 <xref rid="cphc202000498-bib-0077" ref-type="ref">
  <sup>77</sup>
 </xref>]
